Defendant Deandre J Perry in court with attorney Andrew J Golden.  Defendant Deandre J Perry in custody.  Kimberly D Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to negotiations, the State moved to dismiss but read in Count 2.  Court granted State's motion and ordered Count 2 dismissed but read in.

AS TO COUNT 01:
Plea hearing proceeds. Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty of Count 1 as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Ms. Lisa P. The Court imposed the following sentence:

Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be two (2) years consecutive to 13CF4305.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for one (1) year.  Defendant shall serve one (1) year on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.    The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program AND -the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 * Court ordered defendant to pay a DNA surcharge, plus all costs and disbursements from prison funds not to exceed 25%.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - Undergo a mental health asssessment and follow any treatment regimen;
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for his mental or physical needs; take as prescribed and only for as long as deemed medically necessary;
 - No alcohol;
 - Urine screens;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Be given parenting classes/counseling;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Pay balance remaining of costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.


Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
